[[Category:Introduction to Genetics and Evolution|books]]
## Optional Supplementary Text Readings

* Jerry A. Coyne: [Why Evolution Is True](http://www.amazon.com/Why-Evolution-True-Jerry-Coyne/dp/B002ZNJWJU)
* Anthony J.F. Griffiths: [Introduction to Genetic Analysis](http://www.amazon.com/Introduction-Genetic-Analysis-Anthony-Griffiths/dp/1429229438/)
* Scott Freeman: [Evolutionary Analysis](http://www.amazon.com/Evolutionary-Analysis-Scott-Freeman/dp/0132275848/)

## Popular books on Evolution

* Ernst Mayr: [What Evolution Is](http://www.amazon.com/What-Evolution-Is-Ernst-Mayr/dp/0465044255/ref=wl_it_dp_o_pC_nS_nC?ie=UTF8&colid=NNPYAT3YIEQ9&coliid=I3BTH0VQEK8JE0)
* Carl Zimmer: [At the Water's Edge : Fish with Fingers, Whales with Legs, and How Life Came Ashore but Then Went Back to Sea](http://www.amazon.com/At-Waters-Edge-Fingers-Whales/dp/0684856239/ref=wl_it_dp_o_pdT1_nS_nC?ie=UTF8&colid=NNPYAT3YIEQ9&coliid=I1C939R6SLD00K)
* Carl Zimmer: [Evolution: The Triumph of an Idea](http://www.amazon.com/Evolution-Triumph-Idea-Carl-Zimmer/dp/0060958502/ref=wl_it_dp_o_pC_nS_nC?ie=UTF8&colid=NNPYAT3YIEQ9&coliid=I3OQ4UG7CZZ70E)
* Sean B. Carroll: [Endless Forms Most Beautiful: The New Science of Evo Devo and the Making of the Animal Kingdom](http://www.amazon.com/Endless-Forms-Most-Beautiful-Science/dp/0393060160/ref=wl_it_dp_o_pC_S_nC?ie=UTF8&colid=NNPYAT3YIEQ9&coliid=I3H4Z8D5WOKW6W)
* Richard Dawkins: [The Ancestor's Tale: A Pilgrimage to the Dawn of Evolution](http://www.amazon.com/The-Ancestors-Tale-Pilgrimage-Evolution/dp/061861916X/ref=wl_it_dp_o_pdT1_nS_nC?ie=UTF8&colid=NNPYAT3YIEQ9&coliid=I3K3EYDZRGIE95)
* Richard Dawkins: [The Selfish Gene](http://www.amazon.com/The-Selfish-Gene-Edition-Introduction/dp/0199291152/ref=wl_it_dp_o_pdT1_nS_nC?ie=UTF8&colid=NNPYAT3YIEQ9&coliid=I1EDG6HDI9KOAX)
* Richard Dawkins: [The Greatest Show on Earth: The Evidence for Evolution](http://www.amazon.com/Greatest-Show-Earth-Evidence-Evolution/dp/1416594795/)
* Richard Fortey: [Life: A Natural History of the First Four Billion Years of Life on Earth](http://www.amazon.com/Life-Natural-History-First-Billion/dp/037570261X/ref=wl_it_dp_o_pC_S_nC?ie=UTF8&colid=NNPYAT3YIEQ9&coliid=I3MDD8OE7U91UN)
* Richard Fortey: [Trilobite!: Eyewitness to Evolution](http://www.amazon.com/Trilobite-Eyewitness-Evolution-Richard-Fortey/dp/0375406255/ref=wl_it_dp_o_pC_nS_nC?ie=UTF8&colid=NNPYAT3YIEQ9&coliid=I2EI5DU2H6Q4QP)
* Steve Jones: [Darwin's Ghost: The Origin of Species Updated](http://www.amazon.com/Darwins-Ghost-Origin-Species-Updated/dp/0345422775/ref=wl_it_dp_o_pC_S_nC?ie=UTF8&colid=NNPYAT3YIEQ9&coliid=IC4SX8U662AEP)
* Jared M. Diamond: [The Third Chimpanzee: The Evolution and Future of the Human Animal](http://www.amazon.com/s/ref=ntt_athr_dp_sr_1?_encoding=UTF8&field-author=Jared%20M.%20Diamond&ie=UTF8&search-alias=books&sort=relevancerank)
* Carl Sagan: [The Dragons of Eden: Speculations on the Evolution of Human Intelligence](http://www.amazon.com/Dragons-Eden-Speculations-Evolution-Intelligence/dp/0345346297/ref=sr_1_1?s=books&ie=UTF8&qid=1350341855&sr=1-1&keywords=dragons+of+eden)
* Daniel Dennet: [Darwin's Dangerous Idea: Evolution and the Meanings of Life](http://www.amazon.com/DARWINS-DANGEROUS-IDEA-EVOLUTION-MEANINGS/dp/068482471X/ref=sr_1_5?s=books&ie=UTF8&qid=1350341935&sr=1-5&keywords=the+most+dangerous+idea)
* Stephen Jay Gould: [Bully for Brontosaurus: Reflections in Natural History](http://www.amazon.com/Bully-Brontosaurus-Reflections-Natural-History/dp/039330857X/ref=sr_1_1?s=books&ie=UTF8&qid=1350342315&sr=1-1&keywords=bully+for+brontosaurus)
* Matt Ridley: [Genome: The Autobiography of a Species in 23 Chapters](http://www.amazon.com/Genome-Autobiography-Species-Chapters-P-S/dp/0060894083/)
* Jonathan Weiner: [The Beak of the Finch: A Story of Evolution in Our Time](http://www.amazon.com/Beak-Finch-Story-Evolution-Time/dp/067973337X)
* Olivia Judson: [Dr. Tatiana's Sex Advice to All Creation: The Definitive Guide to the Evolutionary Biology of Sex](http://www.amazon.com/Dr-Tatianas-Sex-Advice-Creation/dp/0805063323)

